import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react"; import axios from "axios"; import './home.css'; function Home({ email }) { const [userData, setUserData] = useState(null); // State to store user data useEffect(() => { const fetchUserData = async () => { try { const response = await axios.post("http://localhost:8000/", { email }); // Fetch user data from server setUserData(response.data); // Update state with fetched user data } catch (error) { console.error("Error fetching user data:", error); // Log any errors } }; fetchUserData(); // Call fetchUserData function when the component mounts }, [email]); // Run useEffect hook whenever the 'email' prop changes return (
